data.title: Writing Adolescent Fiction/Character names/Dutch
data.text:
These names are used by Dutch, Flemish and Frisian people. Surnames ending in -ckx are peculiar to the Flemish. If you have a teenage character from the Netherlands today, don't name her Aaghie or him Okkert (unless you're writing about a re-enactment group).

Younger people in the Netherlands today are more likely to be named Laura, Denise, Stefanie, Melanie, Susan or Simone than to have a traditional Dutch name. (Exception: Sanne, which is still popular.) Jorien is a name popular among younger Dutchwomen.
